  "text": "Although model-checking of ATL with perfect recall and uniform strategies is undecidable, replacing uniformity with a weaker notion, for example defining it using distributed knowledge, is decidable [CITATION_1] . Similar results hold for RB±ATL with syntactic epistemic knowledge and weaker notions of uniformity, RB±ATSEL [CITATION_2] .",
